The paper deals with the fundamental properties of deep neural networks, specifically feed forward neural networks with ReLU activation functions and differentiable activation functions. It also discusses the recovery of the row span of the innermost weight matrix of the network, which is a problem related to linear algebra. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of span recovery as an attack, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper also deals with the theoretical analysis of deep neural networks, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
